A system used by Sinopec for managing fuel card operations across their stations.

石化盈科信息技术有限责任公司

data.entity_name: 中石化站级管理系统操作手册
data.content:
中石化站级管理系统操作手册
An operations manual for the Sinopec station-level management system, detailing how to operate its functions.

加油站
Refers to the physical locations where the fuel card system and station-level management system are used.<SEP>The gas station where the described activities and operations take place.

加油员
The staff working at the gas station, responsible for refueling and related transactions.

加油站站长
The manager of the gas station, overseeing the operations and staff.

黑名单
A list of blocked or invalid fuel cards that are denied service at the fuel pumps.

黑卡
A fuel card that is blocked or invalid and appears on the black list.

灰名单
A list of fuel cards that have encountered transaction issues and are temporarily locked.

灰卡
A fuel card that is temporarily locked due to a transaction issue and appears on the grey list.

白名单
A list of valid staff cards that can only be used at specific gas stations.

加油卡
IC cards used in the Sinopec fuel card program for refueling services.

用户卡
Type of fuel card issued to individual or multiple users by the oil company for direct use at gas stations.

员工卡
Cards issued to employees for use in the gas station's operations.<SEP>Type of fuel card used by gas station staff for work-related transactions.

维修卡
Type of fuel card used by the company for maintenance and testing of fuel pumps.

验泵卡
Type of fuel card used for metering fuel pumps, typically kept by the station manager or fuel supervisor.

回叫
An event where the management system requests the fuel pump to re-upload transaction data.

TTC
Transaction sequence number used by fuel pumps to maintain a log and check for missing transactions.

交接班
The process where gas station staff exchange shifts, duties, and responsibilities.<SEP>交接班 refers to the handover process between shifts, including the summary and transfer of transaction information.<SEP>交接班是加油站员工在班次更替时进行的一系列流程，包括复核加油流水等。<SEP>交接班是加油站工作人员在班次结束时进行的一项操作，涉及交易的总结和交接。

中国石化
A major oil and petrochemical company in China.

加油机
The machine at gas stations used for dispensing fuel.<SEP>加油机是加油站用来给车辆加油的设备，记录每次交易的泵码数。

管控PC机
The control PC used for managing and overseeing fuel card transactions.

省中心
The provincial center responsible for processing and managing fuel card data.

全国总中心
The national center that oversees and coordinates fuel card operations across the country.

卡
Refers to the fuel cards used in transactions at the gas station.

油枪
The nozzle used for dispensing fuel from the fuel pump.<SEP>油枪, or 'fuel nozzle,' is the part of the fuel dispenser that is used to deliver fuel into vehicles.

油罐
The tank that stores fuel at the gas station.<SEP>油罐, or 'oil tank,' is the container where fuel is stored before it is dispensed into vehicles.<SEP>油罐是加油站储存燃油的容器。

POS机
The point of sale terminal used for processing card transactions.

液位仪
A device used to automatically obtain the oil level in a tank.<SEP>An instrument used for measuring the level of fuel in the storage tanks.<SEP>Equipment used to measure the fuel level in storage tanks.<SEP>用于自动取得油罐中油高的设备。

加油单元
加油单元是加油站内部的一个组织单位，负责维护加油流水等数据的序号。

加油站员工
加油站员工负责执行加油站的日常操作，包括交接班和日结等。

日结
The end-of-day settlement process that involves generating various reports and managing employee cards.<SEP>日结是对加油站一日内所有班次的进销存信息进行汇总，并生成日报表的过程。

第三方支付
第三方支付是指除了加油卡和现金之外的支付方式，如微信、银行卡等。

泵码
泵码, or 'pump code,' is a unique identifier for the pump used in fuel dispensing operations.<SEP>泵码是加油机记录每笔交易后油枪的走字数，用于核对付油量。

一键重启，关机按钮
一键重启和关机按钮是工控机界面上用于重启或关机系统的按钮。

差异数
差异数是加油机走字数与付油合计之间的差额。

尾差数
尾差数是金额合计与单价乘以付油合计之间的差额。

系统操作说明
系统操作说明是指导员工如何使用系统的文档或指南。

系统登录
系统登录是员工通过验证身份进入加油站的计算机管理系统的过程。

数据通信
数据通信是加油站系统与中心或其他系统之间进行数据传输的过程。

监控收银
监控收银是加油站员工通过系统监控和管理收银过程的活动。

扫码支付
扫码支付是顾客通过扫描二维码进行支付的一种方式。

加油流水
加油流水是指加油站在一定时间内的加油交易记录。

发票
发票是加油站为顾客提供的一种交易凭证。

油票
油票是加油站发行的一种预付费凭证。

润滑油
润滑油是加油站提供的另一种产品，用于车辆的润滑保养。

石化网点编码
石化网点编码是用于识别加油站身份的唯一编码。

账号
账号是员工登录系统时使用的识别信息。

密码
密码是保护账号安全的一种验证方式。

系统管理员
系统管理员是负责管理和维护加油站计算机系统的员工。

初始化管理员
初始化管理员是系统首次登录时使用的默认管理员账号。

Oil Products
Refers to the various types of oil products including成品油 (finished oil products) and润滑油 (lubricating oils).<SEP>Refers to the various types of oil products such as成品油 (finished oil products) and润滑油 (lubricating oils).

System Operations
The processes and tasks carried out within the oil station system, such as adding or deleting oil products, adjusting oil information, and equipment maintenance.<SEP>The processes and tasks carried out within the oil station system, such as adding or deleting oil products, and adjusting oil information.

Equipment
Refers to the physical equipment present at the oil station that requires maintenance and management.<SEP>Refers to the physical equipment present at the oil station that requires maintenance.

Oil Station System
A system used by oil stations for managing operations such as oil product adjustments, equipment maintenance, and business management.

灰名单查询
A function within the system used to query gray-listed cards over a certain period or check if a specific card is on the gray list.

黑名单查询
A function within the system used to query if a card is on the black list, either at the provincial or national level.

业务管理
Refers to the overall category of business management functionalities within the oil station system.

常用油品设置
A feature in the oil station system that allows setting up frequently used oil products based on the station's usage.

油品调节
A process in the system for adjusting the information of oil products in the tanks.

设备管理
Refers to the management of equipment information within the oil station system.

设备信息维护
The process of maintaining and updating equipment information in the oil station system.

新增
The act of adding new information or records into the system.

保存
The act of saving information or records in the system.

取消
The act of canceling or discarding unsaved changes in the system.

修改
The act of making changes to existing information or records in the system.

删除
The act of removing information or records from the system.

查询
An event or action where information is retrieved from the system based on certain criteria.<SEP>The act of searching for specific information or records in the system.

油机信息维护
The function that allows for the maintenance of oil dispenser information in the system.

油罐信息维护
The function that allows for the maintenance of oil tank information in the system.

油枪信息维护
The function that allows for the maintenance of fuel nozzle information in the system.

连接配置维护
The function that allows for the configuration and maintenance of connection information in the system.

应用信息维护
The function that allows for the maintenance of application information for terminal connections in the system.

pos机信息维护
The function that allows for the maintenance of POS machine information in the system.

摄像头信息维护
The '摄像头信息维护' is a specific maintenance event for setting up and updating camera information on smart oil machines.<SEP>The function that allows for the maintenance of camera information in the system, limited to smart oil dispensers.<SEP>摄像头信息维护是智能油机的一个功能，用于设置和更新摄像头信息。

POS机维护
POS机维护是一个涉及维护和管理POS机相关信息的功能类别。<SEP>The 'POS机维护' refers to the maintenance category for point of sale (POS) machines, which involves various maintenance activities and settings.

智能油机
智能油机, or 'Smart Oil Machine,' is a type of advanced fuel dispensing machine that requires maintenance and configuration.<SEP>智能油机是一种具有高级功能的油机，支持摄像头信息和油枪位置信息的维护。

油枪位置信息维护
The '油枪位置信息维护' is a maintenance event focused on updating the position information of fuel nozzles on smart oil machines.<SEP>油枪位置信息维护是智能油机的一个功能，用于维护油枪的位置信息。

终端配置
终端配置, or 'Terminal Configuration,' is the process of setting up and maintaining terminal information, including authentication methods.<SEP>终端配置是维护终端信息的过程，涉及认证方式的修改和保存。

初始化维护
初始化维护 involves the initial setup or reset of various parameters in smart oil machines after hardware changes.<SEP>初始化维护是在油机更换主板后进行的一系列维护操作，包括油机、油枪和油罐的初始化。

初始化查询
初始化查询 is the process of checking the records of initialization maintenance activities for smart oil machines.<SEP>初始化查询是查询初始化记录的操作，用于确认维护的历史和状态。

交易流水查询
交易流水查询 is the process of querying and printing detailed records of transactions that have occurred.<SEP>交易流水查询是查询和打印加油站历史交易流水明细的操作。

交易流水错误更正
交易流水错误更正 is the process of correcting errors found in the transaction records of smart oil machines.<SEP>交易流水错误更正是当发现交易流水记录有问题时进行的错误更正操作。

班结
The event of summarizing the incoming oil, sales, and return tank information for a shift to generate a handover report.<SEP>班结 is the process of concluding a shift by summarizing and confirming the transactions that have taken place.<SEP>班结是加油站工作人员在班次结束时进行的总结操作，涉及交易的汇总和确认。<SEP>统计本班次进油、销售、回罐等进销存信息，生成交接班报表的事件。

班次维护
班次维护 involves the manual or automatic updating of shift information to ensure accuracy.<SEP>班次维护是手动或自动维护班次信息的操作，用于确保班次信息的准确性。

油机
油机, or 'fuel dispenser,' is the machine used for dispensing fuel at gas stations.

摄像头
摄像头, or 'camera,' is the device used for security and monitoring purposes at the fuel dispensing area.

主板
主板, or 'motherboard,' is the main circuit board of a computer or device, such as a fuel dispenser.

查询对话框
A dialog box used for entering query conditions such as date and shift number.<SEP>用于输入查询条件的对话框，如日期、班次号。

班次明细记录
A database entry that records detailed information about shifts.<SEP>记录班次详细信息的数据库条目。

复核操作
An operation used to review and confirm shift records.<SEP>用于对班次流水进行复核的操作。

交易流水明细列表
A list displaying detailed transaction flow information.<SEP>显示交易流水详细信息的列表。

泵码交接
The event of exchanging pump codes and querying the handover information of pump codes.<SEP>交接泵码和查询泵码交接信息的事件。

油罐交接
The event of recording and querying the handover of oil tanks.<SEP>油罐的交接录入和查询的事件。

油罐交接录入界面
The interface used for entering oil tank handover information.<SEP>用于录入油罐交接信息的界面。

交班油高
The oil level data at the time of handover.<SEP>交接班时油罐的油高数据。

交班升数
The volume of oil at the time of handover.<SEP>交接班时油罐的油量数据。

支付类型更正
The event of correcting payment types for employee card transaction flows.<SEP>对加油机上送的员工卡交易流水进行支付类型更正的事件。

员工卡交易流水
The transaction flow of employee cards that requires payment type correction.

校验日志查询
A function to query validation logs for checking the consistency of handover reports and transaction flow data.

Cash Payment
Represents transactions where fuel is paid for with cash.

Fuel Ticket Payment
Represents transactions where fuel is paid for with fuel tickets.

Account Payment
Represents transactions where fuel is paid for on account.

IC Card Payment
Represents transactions where fuel is paid for using an IC card.

IC Card Points Payment
Represents transactions where fuel is paid for using IC card points.

Total Fuel Summary
Represents the aggregate total of fuel transactions.

System Validation
The process of validating fuel transaction information within the system.

Business Management Module
A module in the system used for managing business operations, including validation logs.

Fuel Tank Handover
The event of transferring fuel tank responsibilities between shifts.

Shift Handover
The event of transferring responsibilities and information between shifts.

One-Click Shift 结束
A feature that automates the end-of-shift procedures.

Shift Handover Report
A report that summarizes the details of a shift handover.

Real-Time Employee Business Query
A feature that allows for querying real-time business information of employees during a shift.

Daily Settlement
The process of settling all transactions at the end of the day.

Daily Settlement Query
A feature that allows for querying settled transactions based on specific dates and times.

Fuel Payment Daily Report
A report that summarizes fuel payment transactions after daily settlement.

Transaction Validation Log
A log that records the details of system validations performed during transactions.

Shift Change
The act of one shift ending and another beginning, involving the transfer of duties.

Fuel Pump
The equipment used to dispense fuel to customers.

Oil Tank
A generic category for the storage containers used for holding oil, monitored by the system.<SEP>The storage container for fuel within the station.<SEP>The storage containers for oil that are monitored by the Static Liquid Level Monitoring System.

Fuel Station
The facility where fuel is sold and transactions are processed.

Fuel Dispenser
The machine that dispenses fuel into vehicles.

Payment Terminal
The device used for processing payments at the fuel station.

加油信息
加油信息是一个分类，涉及加油站的各种业务操作和管理信息。

付油日报
A daily report that summarizes fuel payment transactions at the gas station.<SEP>付油日报是加油站的一种日常报表， used for tracking fuel payment transactions.

销售日报
A daily report that summarizes sales transactions at the gas station.<SEP>销售日报是加油站的一种日常报表， used for tracking sales transactions.

用户卡销售统计
A feature that statistics the sales of user cards at the gas station.<SEP>用户卡销售统计是加油站的一项功能，用于统计用户卡的销售信息。

销售日报副表
A supplementary sales report that summarizes the fueling situations of user cards.<SEP>销售日报副表是加油站的一种报表，用于汇总用户卡加油情况。

员工管理
A management function that deals with staff information, roles, and card distribution at the gas station.<SEP>员工管理是加油站的一项管理功能，包括员工信息维护、员工角色维护和员工卡分配等。

员工信息维护
A function within staff management for maintaining and querying employee information.<SEP>员工信息维护是用于维护和查询加油站员工信息的功能。

员工角色维护
A function within staff management for assigning permissions to different staff roles.<SEP>员工角色维护是用于为不同员工角色赋予权限的功能。

员工卡分配
A process of assigning employee cards to staff members within the gas station.<SEP>员工卡分配是将员工卡分配给员工的过程，确保员工能正常使用加油机。

系统
The system used for managing the gas station's operations, including report generation and employee management.

报表
Various reports generated by the system to track the station's operations and sales.

角色
Defined roles within the gas station that determine the permissions and responsibilities of staff members.

员工卡信息
A category that encompasses the data and records related to employee cards within the system.

挂失
An event or action where an employee reports their card as lost, rendering it invalid for future use.

分配备用卡
An event or action where a spare card is assigned to an employee.

员工登录信息维护
An event or process where an employee updates their login password.

员工密码重置
An event or action where an employee's password is reset to a default value.

POS管理
A category that encompasses the management and configuration of point of sale (POS) systems.

油枪分配
An event or action where a fuel gun is assigned to a specific employee.

Pos配置
An event or action where the POS configuration file is generated.

出库单查询
An event or action where delivery notes are queried in the system.

出库单查询下载
An event or action where delivery notes are downloaded from a provincial center.

出库单查询关联
An event or action where delivery notes are associated with corresponding records after fuel receipt.

出库单查询删除
An event or action where a delivery note record is deleted from the system.

无货单验收
An event or action where fuel is received without a corresponding delivery note.

进货验收
An event or action where fuel is accepted and recorded in the system after verifying the delivery note and tank information.

Liquid Level Instrument Application System
A system designed for managing the unloading of oil from tankers into storage tanks, recording relevant data, and calculating volumes and losses.<SEP>A system used for managing the selection of delivery orders and tank information for unloading operations, recording data changes, and calculating unloading volumes and losses.

Delivery Order
A document used to match with the current tank truck for unloading operations.

Tank
A container where oil is unloaded, and its basic information is recorded before and after unloading.

Unloading Operation
The process of unloading oil from a tank truck into a tank, including start and end actions with real-time monitoring.

Unloading Record Table
A table where the data regarding unloading operations, including volume and losses, is saved.

Manual Entry
A method to record tank data manually by entering the front and back scale measurements before and after unloading.

Oil Dispenser
The device used to stop the oil flow and stabilize the oil before and after unloading.

Inventory Acceptance
The process of accepting inventory after unloading, which can be queried and printed.

Inventory Acceptance Query
The function to search for inventory acceptance documents based on delivery order number and unloading date.

Inventory Acceptance Printing
The process of viewing and printing a specific inventory acceptance document.

Oil Transfer
The operation of moving oil between gas stations, within a station, or between a station and a virtual oil depot.

加油站管理系统
A system designed for managing the operations of a fuel station, including the tracking of fuel levels and movement of fuel between tanks.

Probe Settings
A category referring to the configuration options for probes used in monitoring systems.

Static Liquid Level Report
A report generated by the system that details the static liquid level measurements of oil tanks.<SEP>The report generated by the system that provides details on the static liquid level of oil tanks.

Time-Interval Selection
A feature of the system allowing users to select specific time intervals for data retrieval.

Tank Number Selection
A feature of the system allowing users to select specific tanks for data retrieval.

Static Liquid Level Monitoring System
A system used for continuously monitoring and generating reports on the static liquid level of oil tanks.<SEP>The system used for monitoring the static liquid level of oil tanks, which includes features for data retrieval and reporting.

Time-Interval Selection Feature
A feature of the Static Liquid Level Monitoring System that allows users to select specific time intervals for data retrieval.

Tank Number Selection Feature
A feature of the Static Liquid Level Monitoring System that allows users to select specific tanks for data retrieval.

Data Retrieval
The process of obtaining specific data from the Static Liquid Level Monitoring System based on user-selected criteria.

Detection Report
The report generated when static liquid level monitoring is ended, indicating the conclusion of the monitoring process.

Inventory Data
The data automatically recorded by the system every 10 minutes, detailing the inventory of each oil tank.
